attributes.action: Let’s Have A General Election Because Parliament Does Not Represent The People
attributes.additional_details:
Jerermy Corbyn wanted one only until yesterday 
Boris is up for one 
Nigel is ready for one 
Let’s do this
attributes.background: Everyone is torn over Brexit. Parliament does not represent us wether your leave or remain. Mps are switching to parties they weren’t elected for, Mps are making independent groups, we did not vote for this shenanigans in the 2017 election. We knew we was voting for WTO rules in 2016. ELECTION TIME
